# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# OS junk
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Backup patterns
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.bak
*.bak-*
*.orig
*.tmp

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Editor scratch
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.swp
*.swo
.idea/
.vscode/settings.local.json

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Build artifacts (none currently produced; placeholder for future)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
dist/
build/
out/
node_modules/

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Spec Kit + Superpowers Bridge per-developer runtime state
# (each developer has their own; never committed)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.specify/bridge-events.jsonl
.specify/bridge-snapshots/
.specify/superpowers-handoff.json
.specify/feature.json

# Local checklist scratch from bridge validation experiments
specs/*/checklists/protocol-quality.md

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Maintainer-only docs (FR-020): release notes, runbooks, working drafts.
# Kept on the maintainer's local disk; not shipped in the repo.
# Exception: docs/demo/ holds README demo assets (tape sources + rendered
# GIFs) that the README references, and docs/release-runbook.md is a tracked
# release gate input used by CI.
# Pattern uses docs/* (not docs/) so the negation below can re-include
# docs/demo/; git refuses to descend into a fully-ignored parent dir.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
docs/*
!docs/demo/
!docs/release-runbook.md

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Spec Kit install-time generated state (003 v0.4.2 FR-006). Each developer's
# install creates these locally via `specify extension add`/`extension list`;
# the source repo should not pin a version. Removed from index in v0.4.2.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.specify/workflows/workflow-registry.json
.specify/workflows/*/workflow.yml
.specify/extensions/.registry
.specify/extensions/.cache/
.specify/extensions/*/.specify-dev/

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Python venv shells at repo root. Some tools (uv, `python -m venv .`) drop
# these here if invoked from the project root; we never want them tracked.
# Anchored with leading slash so a nested `lib/` or `include/` in a subdir
# (e.g. an extension's own scripts dir) stays trackable.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
/lib/python*/
/include/python*/
pyvenv.cfg

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Spec Kit install-time generated state (009 v0.5.x WSL alignment).
# Each developer regenerates these locally via:
#   specify init --here --script <ps|sh> --force
# See AGENTS.md "Supported Host Environments" for bootstrap details.
# Rationale: Q1+Q2 Policy in specs/009-wsl-dev-env-alignment/spec.md —
# user-facing install-state is per-developer, not project-canonical.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.specify/scripts/

# Spec Kit per-developer install configuration (script flavor, integration choice).
.specify/init-options.json
.specify/integration.json
.specify/integrations/*.manifest.json

# Vendor-managed slash-command skill files (regenerated by `specify init` /
# `specify extension add`). The project-owned `speckit-superpowers-bridge`
# skill is EXCLUDED — it stays tracked because it IS the project deliverable.
.claude/skills/speckit-analyze/
.claude/skills/speckit-checklist/
.claude/skills/speckit-clarify/
.claude/skills/speckit-implement/
.claude/skills/speckit-plan/
.claude/skills/speckit-tasks/
.claude/skills/speckit-taskstoissues/
.claude/skills/speckit-git-commit/
.claude/skills/speckit-git-feature/
.claude/skills/speckit-git-initialize/
.claude/skills/speckit-git-remote/
.claude/skills/speckit-git-validate/
.claude/skills/speckit-agent-context-update/
.agents/skills/speckit-analyze/
.agents/skills/speckit-checklist/
.agents/skills/speckit-clarify/
.agents/skills/speckit-implement/
.agents/skills/speckit-plan/
.agents/skills/speckit-tasks/
.agents/skills/speckit-taskstoissues/
.agents/skills/speckit-git-commit/
.agents/skills/speckit-git-feature/
.agents/skills/speckit-git-initialize/
.agents/skills/speckit-git-remote/
.agents/skills/speckit-git-validate/
.agents/skills/speckit-agent-context-update/
.claude/skills/speckit-constitution/
.claude/skills/speckit-specify/
.agents/skills/speckit-constitution/
.agents/skills/speckit-specify/

# Spec Kit 0.9.x extension command skills generated from this bridge's command
# files. The hand-authored short bridge peer remains tracked at
# .{agents,claude}/skills/speckit-superpowers-bridge/SKILL.md.
.claude/skills/speckit-speckit-superpowers-bridge-*/
.agents/skills/speckit-speckit-superpowers-bridge-*/
